data.description: Turn-key 1951 brick ranch style home with a large well-maintained fenced yard, great for entertaining. Thoughtful and tasteful mix of modern design with a few details of original charm such as the gothic arches in the main living room doorways and an original glass block accent window. Brand new fixtures in kitchen and bathrooms. New flooring throughout. Spacious walk-in closet in the master bedroom with an en-suite bathroom. Right off the living area is a lovely bright office with french doors. Walking distance to the Denver Museum of Natural History, and the Zoo! This home is well built,  block structure and brick all around, great insulation and sound value. Washer/dryer,  brand new refrigerator, stainless appliances all included. Sellers are having a new roof installed in the next few weeks. Move in ready! New driveway. Brand new roof and driveway!
